                <h1>Inside a Prison Cell: The Harsh Reality</h1>
                <p>Inside a prison cell, time slows to a crawl. Constrained by cold concrete walls and barred windows, inmates face solitude and reflection. The bed is minimal, the light harsh, and every sound echoes. The atmosphere is thick with tension and uncertainty, creating a stark environment that forces individuals to confront themselves and their choices.</p>
